HEADWORD: Albugineous
<hw>Al`bu*gin"e*ous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Albugo</er>.]</ety> <def>Of the nature of, or resembling, the white
of the eye, or of an egg; albuminous; -- a term applied to textures,
humors, etc., which are perfectly white.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

